From ba966101b06c5e381d4f1ccc087bf265e5dd0b80 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Vic <vic@pgsdf.org>
Date: Thu, 23 Jul 2026 00:09:19 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] Stop tracking build artifacts

The build/, dist/ and user_station.egg-info/ directories were
committed to the repository. The distutils build cache in build/lib
only refreshes files whose source mtime is newer, so it carried a
0.2 era system.py forward and produced a 0.4 egg that lacked
read_login_classes, which crashed the create user dialog. Generated
artifacts do not belong in history; remove them from tracking and
ignore them so a stale cache can never contaminate an install again.
